K. Application Metadata (System Fields)
25. System Tracking Information
Application ID (Auto-generated)

Application Date/Time Stamp

IP Address

Browser/Device Information

Referral Source (Widget, QR Code, Direct Link, etc.)

Campaign Tracking Code (UTM parameters)

Application Completion Time (Minutes from start to submit)

Last Modified Date

Application Version Number

Status History (Timeline of status changes)

Withdrawal Reason (If applicant withdraws)

Rejection Reason (If rejected by company)

Field Types & Validation Rules
Field Types:
Text (Single line)

Text Area (Multi-line)

Number (With min/max validation)

Date (With date picker)

Dropdown (Single select)

Multi-select (Checkboxes)

Radio Buttons (Single choice)

File Upload (With type/size restrictions)

Email (With validation)

Phone (With formatting)

URL (With validation)

Signature (Digital signature pad)

Rating Scale (1-5 stars, etc.)

Yes/No Toggle

Address Group (Composite field)

Validation Rules:
Required/Optional

Minimum/Maximum length

Format (Phone, Email, ZIP, etc.)

Date range restrictions

File type restrictions (.pdf, .doc, .jpg, etc.)

File size limits (e.g., 10MB max)

Conditional requirements (Show field B only if field A = X)

Cross-field validation (End date after start date)

Unique constraint (No duplicate applications from same user for same job)

Privacy & Compliance Flags:
PII Field (Personally Identifiable Information)

EEO Field (Equal Employment Opportunity)

GDPR Sensitive (Special category data)

Background Check Data

Encryption Required

Retention Period (How long to keep)

Auto-delete Date (When to purge)

Exportable (Can be included in data exports)

Mask in Logs (Partially hidden in audit logs)

Field Configuration Options for Companies:
Each company can configure:

Which fields to show (Enable/disable per field)

Field labels (Customize wording)

Placeholder text (Example text in field)

Help text (Instructions below field)

Requirement level (Required, Optional, Conditional)

Section ordering (Rearrange sections)

Field ordering within sections

Default values (Prefill certain fields)

Validation rules (Custom regex patterns)

Visibility rules (Show based on job type, location, etc.)

Smart Field Features:
Auto-complete from profile data

Geo-suggest for city/state based on ZIP

Phone number formatting auto-format

Email suggestion (Gmail, Yahoo, etc.)

Date picker with range limits

File preview before upload

Progress saving (auto-save every 30 seconds)

Field dependency (show/hide based on other fields)

Character counters for text limits

Format validation in real-time

This comprehensive field library allows for any type of application while maintaining flexibility for companies to customize what they need. The system should store all fields in a flexible schema (like key-value pairs with metadata) to accommodate custom fields without database changes.
